JOHANNESBURG – The Royal Bafokeng nation has announced the full transfer and sale of its struggling Premier Soccer League (PSL) outfit Platinum Stars. The sale was made to an undisclosed buyer, the club said in a statement on Wednesday, confirming the news. “It is with mixed feelings that we announce the sale and transfer of ownership of Platinum Stars Football Club, with immediate effect,” according to the statement. READ: Platinum Stars club for sale? Rumours settled "Due to ever-increasing socio-economic challenges and competition in top-flight football, keeping the club afloat and competitive has not been easy.” The club will however remain in its home base Phokeng and will continue using the Royal Bafokeng sports palace for its home matches under the new buyer. eNCA